result.name: Delicious Thai

reviews.text: Boneless hainan chicken was average. Portion was quite generous I must say. Good that they have different spices that you can add yourself. It’s not located on the main street so may be a little difficult to find. Good spot for a quick lunch if you are nearby.

Nice and decent Thai restaurant.
Come Delicious Thai for lunch and tried couple of their set lunch.  Food here is not great, but it's decent. Not really like authentic taste of Thai food, it's more like Hong Kong style.
As the restaurant located at the end of the alley, they also occupied the outdoor spaces.  Indoor tables are packed, usually will need the share the table during lunch.  Price here is reasonable
Good cheap and casual place for food.  Everything we ordered was really tasty. I had the chicken egg curry which was great. Would also recommend the spicy mince dish or hainanese chicken!
I orderd a grilled lemongrass pork chop with flat rice noodle. Noodle is not flat, but it was sooo tasty!

Authentic Thai chefs. They got huge outdoor fans, which is a great idea for the hk summer! You can sit with your dog in the outdoor area which is pet friendly. Ask for a beer tower which is chilled from the inside
